So right now we're looking
into some snap-on clamps,

00:09:16.700 --> 00:09:19.250
like this one.

00:09:19.250 --> 00:09:23.330
It would just be easy to
snap on and off of his crutch

00:09:23.330 --> 00:09:29.040
so that he could take
it off and on the crutch

00:09:29.040 --> 00:09:31.160
very easily and very quickly.

00:09:31.160 --> 00:09:32.535
So I'm going to
pass these around

00:09:32.535 --> 00:09:35.910
for people to look at it.

00:09:35.910 --> 00:09:39.830
Some ideas for the
no-spill solution-- as you

00:09:39.830 --> 00:09:42.370
saw, we were thinking
gyroscope maybe.

00:09:42.370 --> 00:09:44.950
It turns out that that's a
little bit more complicated

00:09:44.950 --> 00:09:47.300
than we thought it would be.

00:09:47.300 --> 00:09:49.200
It's a little touchy.

00:09:49.200 --> 00:09:52.250
So we're trying to look a
little bit in a different way.

00:09:52.250 --> 00:09:55.860
The second thing we
did was the CoverFlex,

00:09:55.860 --> 00:09:57.209
which we showed in the video.

00:09:57.209 --> 00:09:59.500
It takes a little bit of time
to put on and off though,

00:09:59.500 --> 00:10:03.370
so we were looking into some
other ways, which one of them

00:10:03.370 --> 00:10:04.730
is this suction cover.

00:10:07.310 --> 00:10:10.950
So this is a mug, very easy.

00:10:10.950 --> 00:10:12.843
I'm going to pour
some water into it

00:10:12.843 --> 00:10:20.340
and then put one of these
section covers on top of it,

00:10:20.340 --> 00:10:23.200
and no water will spill out.

00:10:23.200 --> 00:10:26.060
So we're hoping that this will
be able to work for his mugs

00:10:26.060 --> 00:10:29.180
as well, and work on
that a little bit.

00:10:29.180 --> 00:10:33.100
Another thing that we're looking
into, which is coming in today,

00:10:33.100 --> 00:10:37.190
is this Spill-Not, which is
a device that's specifically

00:10:37.190 --> 00:10:40.290
made to counteract movement.

00:10:40.290 --> 00:10:42.370
